Bill Cosby's wife invoked the Rolling Stone sexual assault story to defend him
Camille Cosby released a statement Monday defending  from the numerous sexual assault accusations that have been lobbed his way in recent weeks. And she's using another high-profile news story to cast doubt on the alleged victims. She went on to imply that her husband is the true victim in all of this: "None of us will ever want to be in the position of attacking a victim. But the question should be asked — who is the victim?"   
